        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10634",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=user00265",
                        "name": "user00265",
                        "displayName": "Elisamuel Resto",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What you're asking for is to add a functionality to make Zend_Log rotate logs, or add functionality to read splitted logs in a \"rolling\" form?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=user00265",
                        "name": "user00265",
                        "displayName": "Elisamuel Resto",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-07-30T20:10:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-07-30T20:10:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10665",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=superbiji",
                        "name": "superbiji",
                        "displayName": "Superbiji",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "to make Zend_Log rotate logs",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=superbiji",
                        "name": "superbiji",
                        "displayName": "Superbiji",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-08-04T08:16:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-08-04T08:16:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11149",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cyberlot",
                        "name": "cyberlot",
                        "displayName": "Richard Thomas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is really something that in most cases is deligated to the server to handle.\n\nRotating of logs at the application level of a web application would cause a large delay for the user that happened to hit the site and get \"stuck\" with the rotation action.\n\nlogrotate is a good example of handling this at the server level",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cyberlot",
                        "name": "cyberlot",
                        "displayName": "Richard Thomas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-04T09:17:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-04T09:17:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11170",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=superbiji",
                        "name": "superbiji",
                        "displayName": "Superbiji",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi,\nI'm developing software under Linux, I know logrotate\n\nbut my software will be deployed to multiplatform... (esp windows and linux)\nIt will be necessary to let php rotate the log, just like log4php\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=superbiji",
                        "name": "superbiji",
                        "displayName": "Superbiji",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-07T08:01:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-07T08:01:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11171",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cyberlot",
                        "name": "cyberlot",
                        "displayName": "Richard Thomas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Reopening issue, however I don't think it should be part of \"core\" Zend_Log but instead split off into a seperate Zend_Log_Manager type class. This way those who need this functionality can use it but no overhead is added for those that don't",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cyberlot",
                        "name": "cyberlot",
                        "displayName": "Richard Thomas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-07T08:40:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-07T08:40:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
